other_tests.findings: The liver is normal in size and echotexture. A complex hypoechoic lesion measuring 7 mm may represent an atypical hemangioma. The gallbladder is distended with mural thickening and edema. Several non-obstructing stones and a large, 16 mm obstructing stone within the cystic duct are noted. There is small pericholecystic fluid. The common bile duct is dilated to 7 mm.
